<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="2" MadCap:lastHeight="186" MadCap:lastWidth="747" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare">
    <body>
        <p>You can easily <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">create a TOC manually</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">create a browse sequence manually</MadCap:conditionalText>, adding books, as well as links to topics<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2,Snippets.Snippet1">,</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet4">or </MadCap:conditionalText>other <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">TOCs</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">browse sequences</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1,Snippets.Snippet2">, and external files</MadCap:conditionalText>, in any kind of structure you want. Another option is to create <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">a TOC</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">a browse sequence</MadCap:conditionalText> automatically. This method is based on the heading levels in your topics (h1 through h6). When you create <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">TOC</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">browse sequence</MadCap:conditionalText> automatically, you will use some of the same steps that you used when creating <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">a TOC</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">a browse sequence</MadCap:conditionalText> manually; you still add topic entries to <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">a TOC</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">a browse sequence</MadCap:conditionalText> manually. The difference is that the automatic method lets you automatically create sub-entries in <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">a TOC</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">a browse sequence</MadCap:conditionalText> for the subheadings in your topics.</p>
